  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (configuration gap variant)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD solver relies on three tunable configuration parameters: a near-wall mesh refinement level (target y+ ≤ 5), a Lagrangian particle-tracking time-step multiplier (default 0.25), and a hemolysis-index accumulation threshold (ε_H = 1×10⁻⁴ Pa·s). Validation activities were performed at specific settings for the mesh refinement level and the accumulation threshold; however, the particle-tracking time-step multiplier is not pinned in any configuration record and is described only as 'chosen by the analyst at run time'. No bindsConfiguration node or settings manifest is linked from this package, and the ContextOfUse does not constrain which parameter values must be used in deployment. Consequently, a deploying analyst could select a time-step multiplier that differs from the one used during validation without triggering any documented non-conformance.",
