    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are appropriately not assessed per ASME V&V 40 Table 1 guidance for MRL 2 Class II devices. The model correctly identifies worst-case hemolysis operating conditions across the 5 flow-speed combinations with NIH agreement within ±20% and correct geometric rank ordering (Spearman ρ = 0.94). The RH < 1 acceptance criterion is met for all geometric variants tested. The assessment team notes that the near-wall mesh refinement level and hemolysis accumulation threshold are documented in the validation report; the particle-tracking time-step multiplier was recorded as analyst-selected in the validation log entries. The overall evidence package supports acceptance of the CFD model for the stated COU at MRL 2.",
